ref name=Foot02/>\n\n===Additional data===\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Sweden case list}}\n<br />\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Sweden medical cases chart}}\n{{clear}}\n[[File:CoViD-19 SE.svg|thumb|upright=2|centre|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\n\n==Timeline==\n{{expand section|date=March 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n!|Year\n!|Month\n!|Day\n!|Cases and deaths\n!|Responses\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|2019\n!|November\n|17\n|The first known case was retrodated in a Chinese government report to 17 November, but was not recognized at the time.<ref name=\"original_report\">{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3074991/coronavirus-chinas-first-confirmed-covid-19-case-traced-back|title=China\u2019s first confirmed Covid-19 case traced back to November 17|date=13 March 2020|work=South China Morning Post|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313004217/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3074991/coronavirus-chinas-first-confirmed-covid-19-case-traced-back|archive-date=19 March 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n!|December\n|31\n|China contacts the WHO and informs them of \"cases of pneumonia of unknown etiology (unknown cause) detected in Wuhan\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/csr/don/05-january-2020-pneumonia-of-unkown-cause-china/en/|title=WHO &#124; Pneumonia of unknown cause \u2013 China|website=WHO}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n! rowspan=\"35\"|2020\n! rowspan=\"2\"|January\n|16\n|\n|The Swedish Public Health Agency puts forth a press release that it is monitoring the spread of novel coronavirus (nCOV) said to have spread from the [[Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market]] in [[Wuhan]], in [[Hubei|Hubei province]], China. The risk of spread to Sweden is described as \"very low\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/januari/nytt-coronavirus-upptackt-i-kina/|title=Nytt coronavirus uppt\u00e4ckt i Kina \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|31\n|Sweden confirmed the first case of [[COVID-19]]. A woman in her 20s, returning from [[Wuhan]] on 24 January, tested positive for the SARS-CoV-2 virus and was admitted at [[:sv:L\u00e4nssjukhuset Ryhov|Ryhov Region Hospital]] in [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]].<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200131/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-jonkoping-sweden/amp|title=First case of coronavirus confirmed in Sweden|website=thelocal.se|accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"fhm0226\"/> Having isolated herself voluntarily at home upon arriving in Sweden she was deemed not to have posed any transmission risk during travel or during her initial days in Sweden.<ref name=\"fhm0226\" /> The local [[University college (Scandinavia)|university college]] of [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping University|J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]], stated at the time that it had around 200 Chinese exchange students, responding that the woman may have been a student.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jp.se/artikel/forsta-coronafallet-i-sverige-smittade-kvinnan-kan-vara-student-i-jonkoping-krisgrupp-aktiveras|title=F\u00f6rsta coronafallet i Sverige: Smittade kvinnan kan vara student i J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping \u2013 krisgrupp aktiveras|date=1 February 2020|website=J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings-Posten|language=sv-SE|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jp.se/artikel/just-nu-misstankt-fall-av-coronavirus-i-smaland|title=Misst\u00e4nkt coronafall i Sm\u00e5land var falsklarm \u2013 personen inte smittad|date=11 February 2020|website=J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings-Posten|language=sv-SE|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> The woman was declared asymptomatic, but not fully discharged from healthcare services after over one month of care on 3 March.<ref name=\":0\"/> However, viral fragments continued to be detectable with transmission of live viral particles being deemed unlikely.<ref name=\":0\" />\n|\nOn 30 March, the National Public Health Agency requested for the Swedish government to classify \nthe novel disease as a [[notifiable disease|notifiable infectious disease]] in the [[Notifiable diseases in Sweden|Swedish Communicable Diseases Act]] as both [[Notifiable diseases in Sweden#List of notifiable diseases|dangerous to public health]] (''allm\u00e4nfarlig'') and [[Notifiable diseases in Sweden#List of notifiable diseases|dangerous to society]] (''samh\u00e4llsfarlig''), where [[contact tracing]] is required. \n<ref>{{cite web |title=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten f\u00f6resl\u00e5r att nytt coronavirus tas upp i smittskyddslagen \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/januari/folkhalsomyndigheten-foreslar-att-nytt-coronavirus-tas-upp-i-smittskyddslagen/ |website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se |accessdate=1 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Blohm |first1=Lisa |title=Coronavirus p\u00e5 v\u00e4g klassas som samh\u00e4llsfarligt |url=https://www.dagensmedicin.se/artiklar/2020/01/31/coronavirus-pa-vag-klassas-som-samhallsfarligt/ |website=Dagens Medicin |accessdate=1 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\"|February\n|9\n|\n|A Chinese Lantern Festival in J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping was cancelled in response to the first case imported from Wuhan roughly a week previously.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.jp.se/artikel/kinesiskt-firande-stalls-in-i-jonkoping-pa-grund-av-coronaviruset|title=Kinesiskt firande st\u00e4lls in i J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping p\u00e5 grund av coronaviruset|date=7 February 2020|website=J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings-Posten|language=sv-SE|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|17\n|\n|The [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] advised against all trips to the [[Hubei|Hubei province]] in [[China]], as well as non-essential travel to the rest of [[China]] apart from [[Hong Kong]] and [[Macau|Macao]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/kina---avradan/|title=Kina - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=26 January 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|26\n|Following the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|COVID-19 outbreak in Italy]], a 30-year-old man fell ill three days after returning from northern Italy. He tested positive for the virus, and was admitted to [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital]] in [[Gothenburg]].<ref name=\"bolin1\"/><ref name=\"fhm0226\" />\n|\n|-\n|27\n|Five new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"fhm0227\">{{cite web|url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner/|title=Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner|date=27 February 2020|website=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|language=sv|trans-title=Additional cases of covid-19 in several regions|url-status=live|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland Region]] confirmed that three people in their 30s had tested positive in [[Gothenburg]]. Two of them had been in contact with the 30-year-old patient hospitalized the previous day, and one was deemed to have contracted the virus in Italy.<ref name=\":18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200227/five-new-cases-of-the-coronavirus-in-sweden|title=Sweden confirms five new coronavirus cases, including first patient in Stockholm|last=L\u00f6fgren|first=Emma|date=27 February 2020|website=www.thelocal.se|publisher=The Local|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.cision.com/se/vastra-gotalandsregionen/r/tre-nya-bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion--covid-19--i-vastra-gotaland,c3048641|title=Tre nya bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirusinfektion (Covid-19) i V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland|website=News Powered by Cision|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Stockholm Region]] confirmed that one individual who had tested positive for the virus after returning from Iran was admitted to [[Karolinska University Hospital]] for isolation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/02/corona/|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av nya coronaviruset i Stockholm \u2013 patient v\u00e5rdas isolerat p\u00e5 infektionsklinik|date=27 February 2020|website=Region Stockholm|language=sv|trans-title=Confirmed case of the new coronavirus in Stockholm \u2013 patient being treated in isolation at infection clinic|url-status=live|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> [[Uppsala Region]] confirmed that a woman who had traveled to Germany on a business trip, and met with an Italian colleague, had sought medical attention after showing flu-like symptoms. She tested positive and was admitted to [[Uppsala University Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://via.tt.se/embedded/release/patient-med-bekraftat-coronavirus-vardas-pa-akademiska?publisherId=3235664&releaseId=3271133|title=Via TT|website=via.tt.se|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n|The employer's organisation [https://www.almega.se/ Almega] advised its members to stay at home from work for two weeks if they had visited corona risk areas. According to the [[Swedish Social Insurance Agency]] ('''F\u00f6rs\u00e4kringskassan''<nowiki/>') the employee can receive quarantine allowance ('smittb\u00e4rarpenning') if the person has a medical certificate.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Johansson|first=Daniel|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/stanna-hemma-fran-jobbet-och-fa-smittbararpenning|title=Stanna hemma fr\u00e5n jobbet och f\u00e5 smittb\u00e4rarpenning|date=26 February 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=9 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\nt\n'''On 2 March''' the [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] advised against trips to [[Iran]], due to the uncontrolled spread of the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Covid-19]] in the country.<ref>{{cite web|