]] governor Martin Flod\u00e9n tested positive on 6 March following a trip to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riksbank.se/en-gb/press-and-published/notices-and-press-releases/notices/2020/a-riksbank-employee-has-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus/|title=A Riksbank employee has tested positive for the coronavirus|date=9 March 2020|website=Sveriges Riksbank|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> One of the J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping cases is a school bus driver in Gislaved municipality<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gislaved.se/nyheter/2020-03-08-konstaterat-coronavirus-covid-19-i-kommunen|title=Konstaterat coronavirus i kommunen|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and one of the V\u00e4rmland cases is a staff at [[Swedish Civil Contingencies Agency|Myndigheten f\u00f6r Samh\u00e4llsskydd och Beredskap]] (MSB).<ref name=\"svt.se\" />\n|The [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] advised against all non-necessary travel to the city of [[Daegu]] and the province of [[North Gyeongsang Province|Gyeongbuk]] in [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/sydkorea---avradan/|title=Sydkorea - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=6 March 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] advised against all non-necessary trips to northern [[Italy]], specifically the regions of [[Piedmont|Piemonte]], [[Liguria]], [[Lombardy|Lombardia]], [[Emilia-Romagna]], [[Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol|Trentino-Alto Adige]], [[Aosta Valley|Valle d'Aosta]], [[Veneto]], [[Friuli Venezia Giulia]], [[Marche]] and [[Tuscany|Toscana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/italien---avradan/|title=Italien - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=6 March 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> [[Turin]], [[Milan]], [[Venice]], [[Verona]], [[Trieste]] and [[Florence]] are large cities in these regions. The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]], who initiated the recommendation for the [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]], states that the decision is based solely on the strain of the Italian health care system.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/folkhalsomyndigheten-har-rekommenderat-avradan-fran-resor-till-norra-italien/|title=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten har rekommenderat avr\u00e5dan fr\u00e5n resor till norra Italien \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe same day, Swedish National Broadcaster [[SVT]] held a crisis meeting to consider broadcasting the live finals of [[Melodifestivalen 2020]] on 7 March without an audience, as a response to the growing outbreak. The Danish equivalent had recently decided to broadcast [[Dansk Melodi Grand Prix|Their version]] of the finals without an audience. Ultimately, SVT decided to allow the audience to enter the arena, although they advised people who felt sick to stay at home.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Laurell|first=Agnes|url=https://www.dn.se/kultur-noje/danska-melodifestivalen-framfors-utan-publik/|title=SVT inf\u00f6r Melodifestivalen: Stanna hemma om du k\u00e4nner dig sjuk|date=6 March 2020|work=DN|access-date=8 March 2020|url-status=live|last2=Lenas|first2=Sverker|language=sv}}</ref>\n|-\n|7\n|24 new cases were confirmed; three in Scania,<ref name=\"Sk\u00e5ne official 03-07\" /> and 21 in Stockholm.<ref name=\"sll0307\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/fall-av-nya-coronaviruset-i-stockholm-den-7-mars/|title=Fall av nya coronaviruset i Stockholm den 7 mars|date=7 March 2020|website=Region Stockholm|language=sv|url-status=live|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the morning it was reported that all previous cases in Stockholm Region were travel-related or travel-related person-to-person spread.<ref name=\"SRmar07\">{{Cite news|last=Johansson|first=Birgitta|url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=83&artikel=7423462|title=140 fall i Sverige \u2013 80 av dem i Stockholm|work=Sveriges Radio|access-date=7 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref> Screening for coronavirus is included in a statistical sample of patients where routine testing for [[seasonal influenza]] is performed.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Holm|first=Kerstin|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/fhm-infor-stickprover-pa-influensasjuka|title=Vill se om corona g\u00e5tt under radarn|date=7 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=7 March 2020|last2=Wedin|first2=Helena|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nIt was reported that one of the cases confirmed on 6 March in Stockholm had sought care at [[Danderyd Hospital]] in the Stockholm region on 5 March, and was initially not adequately isolated. The person had caught the virus abroad, but outside known risk areas (at the time South Korea, China, Iran and Northern Italy).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/utrikes/senaste-nytt-om-coronaviruset|title=Senaste nytt om coronaviruset|date=24 February 2020|website=SVT Nyheter|language=sv|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314172402/https://www.svt.se/nyheter/utrikes/senaste-nytt-om-coronaviruset|archive-date=14 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"sll0307b\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/person-smittad-av-det-nya-coronaviruset-sokte-vard-vid-danderyds-sjukhus/|title=Person smittad av det nya coronaviruset s\u00f6kte v\u00e5rd vid Danderyds sjukhus|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref> [[Contact tracing]] has begun, with the case marking the second instance of transmission to Sweden from a non-risk area.<ref name=\"sll0307b\" />\n|The Gothenburg hotel [[Clarion Hotel Post]] chose to let 25 of its 200 employees go, as a response to falling demand due to the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=104&artikel=7423354|title=Posthotellet varslar - p\u00e5 grund av corona - P4 G\u00f6teborg|last=Radio|first=Sveriges|website=sverigesradio.se|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|8\n|One new case was confirmed in Uppsala region,<ref name=\"uppsala0308\">{{cite web|url=https://via.tt.se/pressmeddelande/sjatte-fall-av-coronavirus-i-uppsala-lan?publisherId=3235664&releaseId=3271800|title=Sj\u00e4tte fall av coronavirus i Uppsala l\u00e4n {{!}} Region Uppsala|website=via.tt.se|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> five in Scania region,<ref name=\"skane0308\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mynewsdesk.com/se/region_skane/pressreleases/pressbulletin-om-covid-19-8-mars-2979837|title=Pressbulletin om covid-19: 8 mars|last=Presskontakt|last2=044-3093977|website=Mynewsdesk|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> 12 in V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland,<ref name=\"vgr0308\">{{cite web|url=https://news.cision.com/se/vastra-gotalandsregionen/r/8-mars--12-nya-bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion--covid-19--i-vastra-gotaland,c3054769|title=8 mars: 12 nya bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirusinfektion (covid-19) i V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland|website=News Powered by Cision|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> seven in V\u00e4rmland,<ref name=\"varmland0308\">{{cite web|url=https://www.regionvarmland.se/om-regionen/pressrum/Pressmeddelanden/2020/03/sju-nya-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion-covid-19-i-varmland/|title=Sju nya fall av coronavirusinfektion (covid-19) i V\u00e4rmland|website=Region V\u00e4rmland|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> three in \u00d6rebro<ref name=\"orebro0308\">{{cite web|url=https://www.regionorebrolan.se/sv/Om-regionorebrolan/Press/Nyheter/Nyheter-2020/Tre-personer-fran-Orebro-lan-har-testats-positivt-for-coronavirus/|title=Tre personer fr\u00e5n l\u00e4net har testats positivt f\u00f6r coronavirus|website=www.regionorebrolan.se|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> and 14 in Stockholm region.<ref name=\"sll0308\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/fall-av-nya-coronaviruset-i-stockholm-den-9-mars/|title=Fall av nya coronaviruset i Stockholm den 9 mars|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|date=|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref>\n\nTo date, Stockholm region states that of the 115 confirmed cases in the region, 101 people have been infected in Italy or through contact with a person who has visited Italy, 8 cases have been infected in Iran or through contact with a person who has visited Iran, one person has been infected in another European country, and five cases are still under investigation.<ref name=\"sll0308\" /> One of the \u00d6rebro cases confirmed this day is believed to have caught the virus on a trip back from the [[United States|US]], which he/ she arrived back from approximately a week ago. The other two persons are related to this person. Contact tracing has begun around this case,<ref name=\"orebro0308\" /> which is the third case of transmission to Sweden from a non-risk area. The Uppsala case is a senior high school student at [[Celsiusskolan]] in [[Uppsala]].<ref name=\"Carlbaum\" /> The Stockholm region press office did not report cases detected on the afternoon of the 8th, instead reporting an additional 32 cases on the 9th.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/fall-av-nya-coronaviruset-i-stockholm-den-9-mars/|title=Fall av nya coronaviruset i Stockholm den 9 mars|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|access-date=9 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref> One of the \u00d6rebro cases is reported to have visited an open house at the \u00d6rebro University on 4 March. \u00d6rebro region advises any attendees to be attentive to if symptoms arise.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lolk|first=Nils|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/orebro/person-kan-ha-smittat-andra-med-corona-pa-oppet-hus|title=Coronasmittad bes\u00f6kte \u00f6ppet hus i \u00d6rebro|date=8 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=9 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n|A preschool in [[Hisings Backa]], [[Gothenburg]], decided to close for two weeks due to an infected person having been on the premises. The preschool has not said whether the infected person is a child or one of the staff. Children and staff have all been ordered to quarantine themselves at home by [[Smittskydd V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]], and the preschool is undergoing a deep clean. The preschool has five staff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gp.se/1.25071124|title=F\u00f6rskola i Hisings Backa st\u00e4ngd efter coronasmitta|last=Lindblom|first=Fredrik|date=8 March 2020|website=gp.se|language=sv|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the same date, approx. 15 health care staff at [[Danderyd Hospital]] were quarantined after having been in contact with a patient on 5 March who arrived by ambulance to the emergency unit. The patient had not been to a high-risk area and was not initially suspected to have [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], but when the patients health deteriorated hospital staff decided to test the patient for the virus, which showed the person was infected.<ref>{{Cite news|last=TT|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/stockholm/coronasmittad-till-danderyds-sjukhus-15-tagna-ur-tjanst|title=Coronasmittad till Danderyds sjukhus \u2013 15 tagna ur tj\u00e4nst|date=8 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=9 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\n[[Vietnam]] suspends its visa waiver program to Sweden and seven other European countries in response to the number of cases.<ref name=\":6Vietnam\" />\n|-\n|9\n|Five cases were confirmed in Halland (the first in the region),<ref name=\"news - Region Halland\" /> one in V\u00e4rmland,<ref name=\"V\u00e4rmland9\">{{cite web|url=https://regionvarmland.se/om-regionen/pressrum/Pressmeddelanden/2020/03/ytterligare-ett-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion-covid-19-i-varmland/|title=Ytterligare ett fall av coronavirusinfektion (covid-19) i V\u00e4rmland|date=9 March 2020|publisher=Region V\u00e4rmland|language=Swedish|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> seven in V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vgregion.se/aktuellt/nyhetslista/9-mars-sex-nya-bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion-covid-19-i-vastra-gotaland/|title=9 mars: Sex nya bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirusinfektion (covid-19) i V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland|date=9 March 2020|website=V\u00e4stra G\u00f6talandsregionen|language=sv|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref> two in J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping,<ref name=\"rjl.se\" /> two in Uppsala,<ref name=\":10\" /> and 32 in Stockholm (all of which had been confirmed the previous day).<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite news|last=Kudo|first=Per|url=https://www.svd.se/32-nya-fall-av-coronaviruset-i-stockholm|title=32 nya fall av coronaviruset i Stockholm|date=9 March 2020|work=Svenska Dagbladet|access-date=9 March 2020|language=sv|issn=1101-2412}}</ref> A first case of Covid-19 was also reported in S\u00f6rmland,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/sormland/bekraftat-fall-av-coronavirus-i-sormland|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av coronavirus i S\u00f6rmland|last=|first=|date=|website=SVT|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> a first case in Norrbotten,<ref name=\"SVT9\">{{cite news|last1=Larsson|first1=Erica|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/norrbotten/forsta-coronafallet-i-norrbotten|title=F\u00f6rsta coronafallet konstaterat i Norrbotten|date=9 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|publisher=Sveriges Television|last2=Haupt|first2=Inger|language=Swedish}}</ref> five first cases in [[V\u00e4sterbotten]]<ref name=\"vasterbotten0309\">{{cite web|url=https://www.regionvasterbotten.se/bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirus-i-vasterbotten|title=Bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirus i V\u00e4sterbotten|website=Region V\u00e4sterbotten|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> and one first case in \u00d6sterg\u00f6taland.<ref name=\"regionostergotland.se\" />\n\nThe first Halland case is an elementary school student at [[S\u00e4r\u00f6]] school in [[Kungsbacka]] who had travelled to northern Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Tinder Lond\u00e9z|first=Stephanie|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/halland/forsta-coronafallet-i-halland|title=F\u00f6rsta coronafallet i Halland|date=9 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=9 March 2020|last2=\u00c5kergren|first2=Kristian|language=sv|last3=Schwartz|first3=Elin|last4=Str\u00f6mb\u00e4ck|first4=Daniel}}</ref>\n\nOn the same date, V\u00e4rmland had a total of 21 cases, of which 20 had visited northern [[Italy]], and 19 of these were connected to the same bus tour. One case has been infected in the [[Netherlands]]. One of the V\u00e4rmland cases is a teacher at [[Norrstrandsskolans]] junior high school.<ref name=\"Dahlqvist\" /> One of the 21 cases is admitted to [[Karlstad hospital]]. The majority of the cases are from the [[Karlstad]] area.<ref name=\"V\u00e4rmland9\" /> Further, six new cases were confirmed in V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland, of which two are in the [[Skaraborg]] area.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nOn the same date, the first community transmissions were detected in Sweden. Two persons in the Stockholm area who had no known connection to any of the risk areas or an infected person, were found to be infected, both patients at [[Saint G\u00f6ran Hospital|St. G\u00f6ran Hospital]] since Friday 6 March in two different wards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/en-person-smittad-av-det-nya-coronaviruset-vid-capio-st-gorans-sjukhus/|title=En patient p\u00e5 Capio S:t G\u00f6rans sjukhus testad positivt f\u00f6r covid-19|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|access-date=9 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref> Both cases have been transferred to [[Huddinge Hospital]] for further investigation.<ref name=\"Senaste nytt om coronaviruset\">{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/utrikes/senaste-nytt-om-coronaviruset|title=Senaste nytt om coronaviruset|date=24 February 2020|website=SVT Nyheter|language=sv|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314172402/https://www.svt.se/nyheter/utrikes/senaste-nytt-om-coronaviruset|archive-date=14 March 2020|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOne of the cases in V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland was a patient at [[Kung\u00e4lv Hospital]] with signs of respiratory symptoms since approx. a week who was tested for Covid-19 after the decision of the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] on 4 March. This patient was tested on Sunday 8 March and confirmed positive a day later. The patient was immediately transferred to [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital]] and the affected ward at the [[Kung\u00e4lv Hospital]] has been closed for patient admission. Highly exposed staff at [[Kung\u00e4lv Hospital]] have been told to stay home for a while, and contact tracing has begun.<ref name=\"V\u00e4straG\u00f6taland9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vgregion.se/aktuellt/nyhetslista/9-mars-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19-pa-kungalvs-sjukhus/|title=9 mars: Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av covid-19 p\u00e5 Kung\u00e4lvs sjukhus|date=9 March 2020|publisher=V\u00e4stra G\u00f6talandsregionen|language=Swedish|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n|The Health Care Management ('''H\u00e4lso- och sjukv\u00e5rdsledningen''<nowiki/>') in [[V\u00e4rmland]] decided that all health care staff that have visited northern [[Italy]] or other high-risk areas (current and future as announced by the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]]) are to self-quarantine for 14 days due to vulnerable patients they may meet in their line of work. The decision is also based on incidents of transmission from health care staff to patients in [[China]], [[Norway]] and the [[United States]]. An estimate of the number of affected health care staff was not publicly available by this date. Where possible, affected staff are encouraged to work from home and in cases where this is not possible the staff are suspended from work on medical grounds but will maintain salary benefits.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Dahlqvist|first=Maria|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/varmland/presskonferens-om-coronalaget|title=Presskonferens om coronal\u00e4get|date=9 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=9 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nOn the same date, approx. 30-40 health care staff at [[Saint G\u00f6ran Hospital|St. G\u00f6ran Hospital]] in [[Stockholm]] were quarantined after having cared for a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Covid-19]] infected patient. Another patient at the same hospital has been tested and is awaiting results. The hospital immediately went into a state of readiness to handle the situation.<ref name=\"Senaste nytt om coronaviruset\" />\n|-\n|10\n|Three cases were reported in Scania,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mynewsdesk.com/se/region_skane/pressreleases/pressbulletin-om-covid-19-10-mars-2980402|title=Pressbulletin om covid-19: 10 mars|last=Presskontakt|last2=044-3093977|website=Mynewsdesk|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> 60 in the Stockholm region,<ref name=\"v\u00e5rden\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/fall-av-nya-coronaviruset-i-stockholm-den-10-mars2/|title=Fall av nya coronaviruset i Stockholm den 10 mars|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref> 15 in V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland,<ref name=\"vgregion.se\" /> two first cases in S\u00f6rmland region,<ref name=\"S\u00f6rmland10\">{{cite web|url=https://regionsormland.se/nyheter/nyhetslista-2019/ytterligare-fall-med-covid-19-i-sormland/|title=Ytterligare fall med Covid-19 i S\u00f6rmland|date=10 March 2020|publisher=Region S\u00f6rmland|language=Swedish|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> one first case in J\u00e4mtland<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regionjh.se/nyheter/pressmeddelanden/rjhpress/enpersonijamtlandslankonstateratsmittadavcoronaviruset.5.55412b91170402c7d222e632.html|title=En person i J\u00e4mtlands l\u00e4n konstaterat smittad av coronaviruset - Region J\u00e4mtland H\u00e4rjedalen|website=www.regionjh.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> and first three cases in V\u00e4sternorrland region.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rvn.se/sv/Om-regionen/Aktuellt-i-Region-Vasternorrland/Nyheter/tre-personer-i-vasternorrland-smittade-av-coronaviruset/|title=Tre personer i V\u00e4sternorrland smittade av coronaviruset|website=www.rvn.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> Stockholm region announced this day that two of the 207 infected cases in the region were in intensive care.<ref name=\"v\u00e5rden\" /> One of these patients is a patient from the intensive care unit at [[S\u00f6dersjukhuset|S\u00f6dersjukhuset Hospital]] whom was confirmed infected on Monday 9 March, and immediately moved to [[Karolinska University Hospital]] for further isolated intensive care. The patient has relatives whom have recently travelled in Europe, but the hospital announces it is too early to determine whether the patient has been infected by this person. Contact tracing has begun and [[S\u00f6dersjukhuset|S\u00f6dersjukhuset Hospital]] has gone into a state of readiness to handle the situation and are trying to identify people who may have been exposed to the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/en-patient-vid-sodersjukhuset--smittad-av-covid-19/|title=En patient vid S\u00f6dersjukhuset smittad av covid-19|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref> In the Stockholm region, a total of ten patients have been hospitalised.<ref name=\":14\">{{cite web|url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=83&artikel=7425549|title=Coronasmittade patienter intensivv\u00e5rdas - Nyheter (Ekot)|last=Radio|first=Sveriges|website=sverigesradio.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> One of the Stockholm cases is a judge at the [[Svea Court of Appeal]] who was infected on a trip abroad, although not a risk area. Due to this, the court has told 25 staff to self-quarantine and some hearings have been postponed.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Svensson|first=Frida|url=https://www.svd.se/coronasmittad-pa-svea-hovratt--25-personer-skickas-hem|title=Hallengren: \"Vi \u00e4r inne i en ny fas\"|date=10 March 2020|work=Svenska Dagbladet|access-date=11 March 2020|language=sv|issn=1101-2412}}</ref>\n\nIn V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland region, one patient is considered critically ill but stable.<ref name=\":14\" />\n|The [[S\u00f6dersjukhuset|S\u00f6dersjukhuset Hospital]] in Stockholm went into a state of readiness after an ICU patient was confirmed to have Covid-19. The patient was transferred to [[Karolinska University Hospital]] for further isolated intensive care. It is not known whether the patient got the virus from a relative traveling in Europe and whether the patient has infected staff or patients. Approx. 70 staff have been in contact with the patient but the hospital administration has decided to allow them to continue working until they show symptoms of infection.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Derblom Jobe|first=Michelle|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/stockholm/70-medarbetare-pa-sos-i-kontakt-med-coronasmittad-patient|title=70 medarbetare p\u00e5 S\u00f6s i kontakt med coronasmittad patient|date=10 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=11 March 2020|last2=Langert|first2=Danielle|language=sv}}</ref> This decision has received internal criticism from staff of not being forceful enough.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mitti.se/nyheter/forsta-coronafallet-sodersjukhuset/|title=F\u00f6rsta coronafallet p\u00e5 S\u00f6dersjukhuset|website=mitti.se|language=sv-SE|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the same date, the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] raised the level of risk of the virus spreading from \"''high''\" to \"''very high''\", which is the highest level. This comes after news that there are indications of ongoing local transmission in the Stockholm and V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland area.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite news|last=Stefansson|first=Klara|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/risken-for-coronaspridning-i-sverige-hojs-till-mycket-hog|title=Risken f\u00f6r coronaspridning i Sverige h\u00f6js till \"mycket h\u00f6g\"|date=10 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=10 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/flera-tecken-pa-samhallsspridning-av-covid-19-i-sverige/|title=Flera tecken p\u00e5 samh\u00e4llsspridning av Covid-19 i Sverige|last=|first=|date=|website=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=10 March 2020|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAt the same time, the agency advised everyone with respiratory infection, even mild ones, to refrain from social contacts in private and working life- where there is a risk of spreading the virus. They also ask health care staff in nursing homes and caring of elderly to not work if they have any symptoms of respiratory infection. Relatives of elderly should also avoid unnecessary visits at hospitals and in facilities for elderly and never visit if there are any respiratory symptoms.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/flera-tecken-pa-samhallsspridning-av-covid-19-i-sverige/|title=Flera tecken p\u00e5 samh\u00e4llsspridning av covid-19 i Sverige \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter this announcement, Blekinge Health Care Region enforced a total ban on visits by family members and friends at health care and elderly establishments and hospitals in the region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://regionblekinge.se/om-webb-platsen/nyheter/nyheter-och-pressmeddelande/2020-03-10-besoksforbud-i-halso--och-sjukvarden-infors-idag.html|title=Bes\u00f6ksf\u00f6rbud i h\u00e4lso- och sjukv\u00e5rden inf\u00f6rs idag - Region Blekinge|website=regionblekinge.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> Region V\u00e4rmland enforced a similar ban on all visits to hospitals and health care establishments in the region.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Oscarsson|first=Ida|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/varmland/region-varmland-infor-besoksforbud-pa-vardavdelningar|title=Region V\u00e4rmland inf\u00f6r bes\u00f6ksf\u00f6rbud p\u00e5 v\u00e5rdavdelningar|date=10 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=11 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nAfter the announcement of the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] to protect the elderly and the frail, Stockholm Region decided to change their strategy for testing for COVID-19 to mainly focus on the very ill and not just people who had visited risk areas.<ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/sthlm/fyra-akutsjukhus-i-stockholms-lan-i-stabslage-pa-grund-av-coronasmittan/|title=Fyra akutsjukhus i stabsl\u00e4ge p\u00e5 grund av coronasmittan|date=11 March 2020|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> [[Danderyd Hospital]] also went into a state of readiness due to the situation of the Covid-19 spread in Stockholm.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mitti.se/nyheter/danderyds-sjukhus-stabslage/|title=P\u00e5 grund av corona \u2013 Danderyds sjukhus i stabsl\u00e4ge|website=mitti.se|language=sv-SE|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|11\n|144 new infected cases were reported. Blekinge, Dalarna, and V\u00e4stmanland reported their first cases; one, one and four respectively. The first death was reported, in Stockholm, a person in the 70s, believed to have been infected through community approx. spread a week earlier.<ref name=\":33\" /> The government also determined that testing should be limited to people who are perceived to be at greatest risk.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/sthlm/farre-kommer-att-provtas-for-coronaviruset-i-stockholm/|title=F\u00e4rre kommer att provtas f\u00f6r coronaviruset i Stockholm|date=12 March 2020|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March Stockholm region decided to only test hospitalised patients from risk groups and health care staff with symptoms. Other regions will follow suit within the coming week. This means the data on the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]]<nowiki/>s website is not reflecting the actual infected persons in the country since local transmission has been ongoing since at least early March.''<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite news|last=Almgren|first=Jan|url=https://www.svd.se/uppmaningen-kom-inte-in-for-provtagning|title=Uppmaningen: Kom inte in f\u00f6r provtagning|date=12 March 2020|work=Svenska Dagbladet|access-date=14 March 2020|language=sv|issn=1101-2412}}</ref><ref name=\":30\">{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/6j7KW3|title=Sk\u00e5ne stoppar allm\u00e4nt coronaprov|website=Aftonbladet|language=sv|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":35\">{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/70GQRV|title=Nya strategin - slutar r\u00e4kna exakta antalet coronafall|website=Aftonbladet|language=sv|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>'''\n|The Stockholm region decided to only test hospitalised patients from risk groups and health care staff with symptoms. Other regions will follow suit within the coming week. This means the data on the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]]<nowiki/>s website is not reflecting the actual infected persons in the country, since local transmission has been ongoing since at least early March.<ref name=\":8\" /><ref name=\":30\" /><ref name=\":35\" />\n\nThe same date, [[S\u00f6dert\u00e4lje Hospital]] went into a state of readiness due to the situation in Stockholm region.<ref name=\":17\" />\n\nThe government has banned all gatherings larger than 500 people, under threat of fines and a six-month prison sentence.<ref name=\":34\">{{Cite news|last=V. Nyheter|first=S.|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/snabbkollen/regeringen-stoppar-stora-moten|title=Regeringen stoppar stora m\u00f6ten|date=11 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=11 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nThe same date, the government announced that the qualifying day of sickness ('''karensdag''<nowiki/>') will be temporarily abolished in order to ensure that people feeling slightly ill will stay at home from work. This means that the state will pay sick pay allowance from the first day the employee is absent from work. The decision is effective as of 11 March 2020 and is believed to reduce the virus spreading as well as the burden on the health care system.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.krisinformation.se/nyheter/2020/mars/slopad-karensdag|title=Slopad karensdag med anledning av coronaviruset|website=www.krisinformation.se|language=sv|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|12\n|Gotland identified the first two infected persons on the island; two non-related men who had returned from travel to risk-areas abroad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Gelin|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/ost/forsta-coronafallen-konstaterade-pa-gotland|title=Tv\u00e5 coronafall konstaterade p\u00e5 Gotland|date=12 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=16 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|13\n|\n|The government decided to temporarily abolish the demand of a doctor's certificate for 14 days for people staying home from work due to illness (i.e. sick pay period). Previously a doctor's certificate was needed after seven days.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Olsson|first=Jonas|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/regeringen-kravet-pa-lakarintyg-vid-sjukdom-avskaffas|title=Regeringen: Kravet p\u00e5 sjukintyg avskaffas tillf\u00e4lligt|date=13 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=13 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] also declared the same date that stopping the spread of Covid-19 has entered a \"new phase\" which requires \"other efforts\". The continued focus is now to delay spread among the population and to protect the elderly and most vulnerable against the disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/ny-fas-kraver-nya-insatser-mot-covid-19/|title=Ny fas kr\u00e4ver nya insatser mot covid-19 \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> On the same date, 814 persons in Sweden had been confirmed sick with Covid-19. Stockholm region has since 11 March only tested persons from risk groups and health care staff with symptoms.<ref name=\":8\" /> On 12 March, Scania region decided to do the same, and the other regions in Sweden will follow suit within a week.<ref name=\":30\" /><ref name=\":35\" />\n\nOn the same date, media reported that there is a shortage in personal protective equipment (PPE) for health care staff, and hospitals in Stockholm have been forced to reuse disposable PPEs after sanitation. The regional Health Care Director warned about this scenario in early March and government agencies have temporarily waived the public procurement law in order to hastily procure more supplies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/nyheter/coronaviruset/vardforraden-borjar-sina-engangsskydd-ateranvands/|title=Sjukhusens f\u00f6rr\u00e5d b\u00f6rjar sina \u2013 eng\u00e5ngsskydd \u00e5teranv\u00e4nds i Stockholm|website=www.expressen.se|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> The [[National Board of Health and Welfare (Sweden)|National Board of Health and Welfare]] ('''Socialstyrelsen''<nowiki/>') confirmed that there is no preparedness storage and nothing to distribute to the health care sector.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/tv/nyheter/coronaviruset/socialstyrelsen-det-finns-ingenting-att-distribuera/|title=Covid-19: Brist p\u00e5 skyddsutrustning och provtagningsmaterial|website=Expressen TV|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/lA5mAo|title=Larmet inifr\u00e5n v\u00e5rden: \"Finns ingen skyddsutrustning\"|website=Aftonbladet|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|14\n|The second death in Sweden was reported on 14 March, an 85-year-old woman in the V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland area belonging to a risk group,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Svensson|first=Ellinor|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/vast/svensk-kvinna-dod-i-corona|title=Svensk kvinna d\u00f6d i corona|date=14 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=15 March 2020|last2=Tinder Lond\u00e9z|first2=Stephanie|language=sv}}</ref> and the third the same day, an elderly person in the Stockholm region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/aldre-patient-med-covid-19-har-avlidit/|title=\u00c4ldre patient med covid-19 har avlidit|last=v\u00e5rden|first=Hitta r\u00e4tt i|last2=resa|first2=Planera din|website=www.sll.se|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020|last3=sjukresor|first3=F\u00e4rdtj\u00e4nst och|last4=cookies|first4=Om|last5=webbplatsen|first5=Om|last6=Prenumerera|last7=Anslagstavla|last8=Telefon: 08-737 25 00|last9=regionstockholm@sll.se|first9=E.-post}}</ref>\n|The [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] advised against all non-necessary trips abroad, in other words visits and tourist travel. The recommendation is valid until at least 14 April, when a new decision will be taken.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Makar|first=Maria|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/coronaviruset-ud-avrader-fran-icke-nodvandiga-resor-till-alla-lander|title=Coronaviruset \u2013 UD avr\u00e5der fr\u00e5n icke n\u00f6dv\u00e4ndiga resor till alla l\u00e4nder|date=14 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=15 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n|-\n|15\n|\n|\n|-\n|16\n|\n|The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] recommended that people over 70 should limit close contact with other people, and employers should recommend their employees work from home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/personer-over-70-bor-begransa-sociala-kontakter-tills-vidare/|title=Personer \u00f6ver 70 b\u00f6r begr\u00e4nsa sociala kontakter tills vidare \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se}}</ref>\n|-\n|17\n|\n|The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] recommended that secondary schools and universities use distance learning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/larosaten-och-gymnasieskolor-uppmanas-nu-att-bedriva-distansundervisning/|title=L\u00e4ros\u00e4ten och gymnasieskolor uppmanas nu att bedriva distansundervisning \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se}}</ref>\n|-\n|18\n|\n|\n|-\n|19\n|\n|The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] recommended that people avoid unnecessary weekend trips within Sweden<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/tank-over-om-resan-verkligen-ar-nodvandig|title=T\u00e4nk \u00f6ver om resan verkligen \u00e4r n\u00f6dvandig|date=19 March 2020|language=sv|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|20\n|\n|\n|-\n|21\n|\n|\n|-\n|22\n|\n|\n|-\n|23\n|The country exceeded more than 2,000 cases which was the second milestone in only one week since the country reached 1,000 cases on 15 March 2020. Death toll hit the record of 10 deaths in one day.{{source needed|date=April 2020}}\n|\n|-\n|24\n|\n|New restrictions are put in by the government only allowing restaurants to serve customers at a table, not allowing serving at a bar or other types of serving where many people are close to each other. Restaurants are also recommended to place tables further away from each other. Disease control holds the power together with responsible municipalities to close down businesses that do not follow the regulations <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nya-forbudet-endast-bordsservering-tillats-pa-restauranger-och-barer|title=Nya restriktioner: Endast bordsservering till\u00e5ts p\u00e5 restauranger och barer|date=24 March 2020|language=sv|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|25\n|Death toll hit more than 20 new deaths in one day.{{source needed|date=April 2020}}\n|\n|-\n|26\n|\n|\n|-\n|27\n|The country exceeded more than 3,000 cases, four days after the milestone of 2,000 cases was reached (on 23 March 2020).{{source needed|date=April 2020}}\n|The government announce a ban for all gatherings larger than 50 people starting Sunday 29 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/artiklar/2020/03/andring-i-forordning-om-forbud-mot-att-halla-allmanna-sammankomster-och-offentliga-tillstallningar|title=\u00c4ndring i f\u00f6rordning om f\u00f6rbud mot att h\u00e5lla allm\u00e4nna sammankomster och offentliga tillst\u00e4llningar|date=27 March 2020|language=sv|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n!  rowspan=\"1\"|April\n|1\n|Death toll hit more than 50 new deaths in one day.{{source needed|date=April 2020}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{clear}}\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=Foot01>The jump of deaths between 29 and 30 Mars is explained by not all cases being reported during the previous days.</ref>\n<ref name=Foot02>Source for numbers: [https://experience.arcgis.com/experience/09f821667ce64bf7be6f9f87457ed9aa Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten]</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.krisinformation.se/en/hazards-and-risks/disasters-and-incidents/2020/official-information-on-the-new-coronavirus Emergency Information from Swedish Authorities: Official information on the novel corona Virus] from The [[Swedish Civil Contingencies Agency]] \u2013 ''Myndigheten f\u00f6r samh\u00e4llsskydd och beredskap''.\n* [https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/smittskydd-beredskap/utbrott/aktuella-utbrott/covid-19/ Information om Coronavirus covid-19] from The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] \u2013 ''Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten'' (In Swedish).\n* [https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/the-public-health-agency-of-sweden/communicable-disease-control/covid-19/ FAQ about COVID-19] on The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] \u2013 ''Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten''.\n* [https://www.1177.se/Vastra-Gotaland/sjukdomar--besvar/infektioner/ovanliga-infektioner/covid-19